# Network Switches

## What is a Switch?

A network switch connects devices within the same Local Area Network (LAN).

It forwards Ethernet frames based on MAC addresses.

---

## CAM Table

A switch builds a CAM (Content Addressable Memory) table to map MAC addresses to switch ports.

Example:

MAC Address -> Port

AA:BB:CC:11:22:33 -> Port 1

---

## Advantages

- Faster communication
- Fewer collisions
- Better bandwidth utilization
- Improved security compared to hubs

---

## Hub vs Switch

| Hub | Switch |
|------|---------|
| Sends data to every device | Sends only to the destination |
| No CAM table | Uses CAM table |
| Slower | Faster |

---

## Key Takeaways

- Switches operate at Layer 2.
- Switches use MAC addresses.
- CAM tables improve network efficiency.
